Package: cfbseedR
Title: Functions to Efficiently Simulate and Evaluate College Football
    Seasons
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Saiem", "Gilani", email = "saiem.gilani@gmail.com",
           role = c("cre", "aut"),
           comment = "Adapted from nflseedR by Sebastian Carl and Lee Sharpe")
Description: A set of functions to simulate college football seasons and
    compute standings, conference ranks, conference champions, and College
    Football Playoff seeds. The package is an adaptation of the 'nflseedR'
    package by Sebastian Carl and Lee Sharpe (MIT licensed) with college
    football semantics: conferences instead of divisions, independents,
    conference championship games, and 12-team playoff straight seeding.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/sportsdataverse/cfbseedR,
    https://cfbseedR.sportsdataverse.org
BugReports: https://github.com/sportsdataverse/cfbseedR/issues
